{"id": 57665, "date": "2025-07-10T04:00:36", "date_gmt": "2025-07-10T11:00:36", "guid": {"rendered": "https://estreetshuffle.com/?p=57665"}, "modified": "2026-03-02T15:24:49", "modified_gmt": "2026-03-02T23:24:49", "slug": "kingdom-of-days-july-10-2", "status": "publish", "type": "post", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2025/07/10/kingdom-of-days-july-10-2/", "title": {"rendered": "July 10"}, "content": {"rendered": "<p><strong>1966:\u00a0</strong>The Castiles play a brief set at the Surf &#8216;N&#8217; See Club in Sea Bright, New Jersey.</p>\n<p><strong>1971:\u00a0</strong>The Bruce Springsteen Band makes its debut, headlining at Brookdale Community College&#8217;s 2nd Annual &#8220;Nothing&#8217;s Festival&#8221; in Lincroft, New Jersey. (There wasn&#8217;t a first annual festival, and the show is free and unpaid&#8211;but a gig&#8217;s a gig.)</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/AqnlX8oq-2g?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/zWURsgK_-4M?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/r6all5hMCWY?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-attachment-id=\"19469\" data-permalink=\"https://estreetshuffle.com/1971-07-10-2/\" data-orig-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/1971-07-10.jpg?fit=1258%2C438&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"1258,438\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;Ken Rosen&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1593117635&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"1971-07-10\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/1971-07-10.jpg?fit=300%2C104&amp;ssl=1\" data-large-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/1971-07-10.jpg?fit=758%2C264&amp;ssl=1\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-19469 size-full\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/1971-07-10.jpg?resize=758%2C264&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"758\" height=\"264\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/1971-07-10.jpg?w=1258&amp;ssl=1 1258w, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/1971-07-10.jpg?resize=300%2C104&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/1971-07-10.jpg?resize=1024%2C357&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/1971-07-10.jpg?resize=768%2C267&amp;ssl=1 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 758px) 100vw, 758px\" /></p>\n<p><strong>1983:\u00a0</strong>Bruce joins Cats on a Smooth Surface for five songs at The Stone Pony in Asbury Park, including &#8220;Wooly Bully&#8221; and &#8220;Little Latin Lupe Lu.&#8221;</p>\n<p><strong>1987:\u00a0</strong>Columbia Records producer, executive, and Bruce Springsteen-signer John Hammond passes away at the age of 76.\u00a0Here&#8217;s Bruce talking about his admiration for Hammond in an early interview.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/C3OJKnbSQb0?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-attachment-id=\"19470\" data-permalink=\"https://estreetshuffle.com/1987-07-10/\" data-orig-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/1987-07-10.jpg?fit=1254%2C977&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"1254,977\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;Ken Rosen&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1593118036&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"1987-07-10\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/1987-07-10.jpg?fit=300%2C234&amp;ssl=1\" data-large-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/1987-07-10.jpg?fit=758%2C591&amp;ssl=1\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-19470 size-full\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/1987-07-10.jpg?resize=758%2C591&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"758\" height=\"591\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/1987-07-10.jpg?w=1254&amp;ssl=1 1254w, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/1987-07-10.jpg?resize=300%2C234&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/1987-07-10.jpg?resize=1024%2C798&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/1987-07-10.jpg?resize=768%2C598&amp;ssl=1 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 758px) 100vw, 758px\" /></p>\n<p><strong>1988:\u00a0</strong>Bruce and the E Street Band play their second of two Tunnel of Love shows at Bramall Lane in Sheffield.</p>\n<div id=\"v-EZbUAKue-1\" class=\"video-player\"><iframe title='VideoPress Video Player' aria-label='VideoPress Video Player' width='758' height='568' src='https://videopress.com/embed/EZbUAKue?hd=1&amp;cover=1&amp;loop=0&amp;autoPlay=0&amp;permalink=1&amp;muted=0&amp;controls=1&amp;playsinline=0&amp;useAverageColor=0&amp;preloadContent=metadata' frameborder='0' allowfullscreen data-resize-to-parent=\"true\" allow='clipboard-write'></iframe><script data-jetpack-boost=\"ignore\" src='https://s0.wp.com/wp-content/plugins/video/assets/js/next/videopress-iframe.js'></script></div>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent&#038;listType=playlist&#038;list=PLJTyL9twk3zATGqy6HjddIRTztJhrdWsH\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-attachment-id=\"52374\" data-permalink=\"https://estreetshuffle.com/the_miami_herald_1988_07_11_9/\" data-orig-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The_Miami_Herald_1988_07_11_9-scaled.jpg?fit=2055%2C2560&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"2055,2560\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"The_Miami_Herald_1988_07_11_9\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The_Miami_Herald_1988_07_11_9-scaled.jpg?fit=241%2C300&amp;ssl=1\" data-large-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The_Miami_Herald_1988_07_11_9-scaled.jpg?fit=758%2C944&amp;ssl=1\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-52374 size-full\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The_Miami_Herald_1988_07_11_9-scaled.jpg?resize=758%2C944&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"758\" height=\"944\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The_Miami_Herald_1988_07_11_9-scaled.jpg?w=2055&amp;ssl=1 2055w, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The_Miami_Herald_1988_07_11_9-scaled.jpg?resize=241%2C300&amp;ssl=1 241w, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The_Miami_Herald_1988_07_11_9-scaled.jpg?resize=822%2C1024&amp;ssl=1 822w, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The_Miami_Herald_1988_07_11_9-scaled.jpg?resize=768%2C957&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The_Miami_Herald_1988_07_11_9-scaled.jpg?resize=1233%2C1536&amp;ssl=1 1233w, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The_Miami_Herald_1988_07_11_9-scaled.jpg?w=1516&amp;ssl=1 1516w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 758px) 100vw, 758px\" /></p>\n<p><strong>1990:\u00a0</strong>Sixteen years after its original release,\u00a0<em>The Wild, The Innocent &amp; The E Street Shuffle</em> is finally certified platinum by the Recording Industry Association of America.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent&#038;listType=playlist&#038;list=OLAK5uy_kVpI9n-dmnHW7df2Iloxk8nXaya4yEzEw\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p><strong>1992:\u00a0</strong>Night Three of five at Wembley Arena on World Tour 1992 features an acoustic &#8220;Dancing in the Dark.&#8221;</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/a-SPT1ZR_Eo?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/EvQUeL841A0?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p><strong>2018:</strong>\u00a0<em>Springsteen on Broadway\u00a0</em>resumes its theatrical run at the Walter Kerr Theater in New York City after a nine-day break. Patti is absent tonight, so Bruce drops their duets and instead substitutes &#8220;Long Time Comin'&#8221; in their place. To make up for playing one fewer song than usual, Bruce adds an encore of sorts: &#8220;This Hard Land.&#8221;</p>\n<div id=\"v-Rt2JA6ng-1\" class=\"video-player\"><iframe title='VideoPress Video Player' aria-label='VideoPress Video Player' width='758' height='758' src='https://videopress.com/embed/Rt2JA6ng?hd=1&amp;cover=1&amp;loop=0&amp;autoPlay=0&amp;permalink=1&amp;muted=0&amp;controls=1&amp;playsinline=0&amp;useAverageColor=0&amp;preloadContent=metadata' frameborder='0' allowfullscreen data-resize-to-parent=\"true\" allow='clipboard-write'></iframe><script data-jetpack-boost=\"ignore\" src='https://s0.wp.com/wp-content/plugins/video/assets/js/next/videopress-iframe.js'></script></div>\n<p><strong>2019:\u00a0</strong>Bruce breaks news when he calls in to E Street Radio: a new film is on the way, a concert film based on\u00a0<em>Western Stars,\u00a0</em>directed by Thom Zimny. When it&#8217;s released later in the year, Bruce will take a co-director credit.</p>\n<audio class=\"wp-audio-shortcode\" id=\"audio-57665-12\" preload=\"none\" style=\"width: 100%;\" controls=\"controls\"><source type=\"audio/mpeg\" src=\"https://estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/2019-07-10-Bruce-on-E-St-Radio.mp3?_=12\" /><a href=\"https://estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/2019-07-10-Bruce-on-E-St-Radio.mp3\">https://estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/2019-07-10-Bruce-on-E-St-Radio.mp3</a></audio>\n<p><strong>2021:\u00a0</strong><em>Springsteen on Broadway\u00a0</em>continues its limited return engagement at the St. James Theater in New York City.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n", "protected": false}, "excerpt": {"rendered": "<p>The Bruce Springsteen Band debuted on this date in 1971. Listen to their first performance inside, plus more highlights from this date in history.</p>\n", "protected": false}, "author": 1, "featured_media": 11211, "comment_status": "open", "ping_status": "open", "sticky": false, "template": "", "format": "standard", "meta": {"_monsterinsights_skip_tracking": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_active": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_note": "", "_monsterinsights_sitenote_category": 0, "jetpack_post_was_ever_published": false, "_jetpack_newsletter_access": "", "_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs": false, "_jetpack_newsletter_tier_id": 0, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paywalled_content": false, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paid_content": false, "footnotes": "", "jetpack_publicize_message": "", "jetpack_publicize_feature_enabled": true, "jetpack_social_post_already_shared": true, "jetpack_social_options": {"image_generator_settings": {"template": "highway", "default_image_id": 0, "font": "", "enabled": false}, "version": 2}}, "categories": [2], "tags": [534, 640, 1260, 1261, 836, 707, 690, 11, 1102, 706, 1249, 2416, 985], "class_list": ["post-57665", "post", "type-po